Aim
To perform an aggressive Nmap scan using the -A option and analyze operating system details, service
versions, and traceroute information.
Introduction
Nmap aggressive scan is used to gather advanced information about a target system. The -A option enables:
• Operating system detection
• Service version detection
• Script scanning
• Traceroute
This scan helps cybersecurity professionals identify detailed information about a target machine and possible
vulnerabilities.
Procedure
Step 1: Install Nmap
Open Kali Linux terminal and install Nmap:
sudo apt install nmap -y
Step 2: Verify Installation
Check whether Nmap is installed successfully:
nmap --version
Step 3: Perform Aggressive Scan
Run the following command:
sudo nmap -A www.grace.edu.in
Step 4: Analyze the Output
Observe:
• Open ports
• Service versions
• Operating system details
• Traceroute information
Implementation
Command Used
sudo nmap -A www.grace.edu.in
Explanation
• sudo → Runs command with administrator privileges
• nmap → Starts Nmap tool
• -A → Enables aggressive scan
• www.grace.edu.in → Target website/domain
Output
PORT STATE SERVICE VERSION
21/tcp open ftp
80/tcp open http
